    "id": 30,
    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks - April 30, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-30",
    "tags": ["GPT-5.5", "Biosecurity", "OpenAI-Microsoft", "Anthropic", "AI exports", "UK AI hardware"],
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - April 30, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 GPT-5.5 landed as OpenAI's new workhorse and brought a benchmark parade with it\n\nThe frontier labs have stopped pretending to be modest. We now launch models with a spreadsheet and a victory lap.\n\n- **The rollout:** OpenAI released GPT-5.5 on April 23, 2026 to ChatGPT and Codex, with GPT-5.5 Pro rolling out in ChatGPT and API availability coming after additional safety work.\n- **The scorecard:** OpenAI says GPT-5.5 reached 82.7% on Terminal-Bench 2.0, 58.6% on SWE-Bench Pro, 78.7% on OSWorld-Verified, and 84.4% on BrowseComp while keeping GPT-5.4-class latency and using fewer tokens on Codex tasks.\n\n*The new baseline is apparently: do real work, use tools, and show the receipts.*\n\n**Sources:** [Introducing GPT-5.5](https://openai.com/index/introducing-gpt-5-5/) | [GPT-5.5 System Card](https://deploymentsafety.openai.com/gpt-5-5/internal-research-debugging-evaluation)\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 OpenAI also opened a GPT-5.5 bio jailbreak contest because normal bug bounties were too ordinary\n\nLaunching the model and then paying researchers to break its bio safeguards is at least a refreshingly direct form of confidence.\n\n- **What is in scope:** OpenAI's GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty, announced April 23, 2026, asks vetted researchers to find one universal jailbreak that clears all five bio safety questions in a clean chat on GPT-5.5 in Codex Desktop.\n- **What is on the line:** the first true universal jailbreak pays $25,000, applications stay open until June 22, 2026, and testing runs from April 28 to July 27 under NDA.\n\n*AI safety now comes with prize money, application windows, and a slightly unnerving amount of specificity.*\n\n**Sources:** [GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty](https://openai.com/index/gpt-5-5-bio-bug-bounty/) | [GPT-5.5 System Card](https://deploymentsafety.openai.com/gpt-5-5/trust-based-access)\n\n---\n\n## 🤝 OpenAI and Microsoft rewired the partnership without actually breaking up\n\nThe relationship has reached that modern phase where both sides want more freedom and still need each other's datacenters.\n\n- **What changed:** On April 27, 2026, OpenAI said Microsoft remains its primary cloud partner and still gets first launch on Azure unless it cannot support the needed capabilities, while OpenAI can now serve products across any cloud provider.\n- **The commercial reset:** Microsoft's license to OpenAI IP now runs through 2032 on a non-exclusive basis, Microsoft no longer pays revenue share to OpenAI, and OpenAI's own revenue-share payments to Microsoft continue through 2030 with a cap.\n\n*When the AI stack gets big enough, even the alliances need their own governance layer.*\n\n**Sources:** [The next phase of the Microsoft OpenAI partnership](https://openai.com/index/next-phase-of-microsoft-partnership/) | [OpenAI company updates](https://openai.com/)\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Anthropic and Amazon turned a cloud deal into a gigawatt-scale compute reservation\n\nWe are well past startup cloud credits. Frontier labs now reserve infrastructure like small countries plan electricity.\n\n- **The new agreement:** Anthropic announced on April 20, 2026 that it had signed a new deal with Amazon securing up to 5 gigawatts of capacity to train and deploy Claude, including Trainium2 capacity in the first half of 2026 and nearly 1 GW of Trainium2 and Trainium3 by year-end.\n- **The scale:** Anthropic said it will commit more than $100 billion over ten years to AWS technologies, currently uses over one million Trainium2 chips, and that Amazon is investing $5 billion now with up to $20 billion more possible.\n\n*The AI race increasingly looks like power procurement wearing an API badge.*\n\n**Sources:** [Anthropic and Amazon expand collaboration for up to 5 gigawatts of new compute](https://www.anthropic.com/news/anthropic-amazon-compute) | [Anthropic newsroom](https://www.anthropic.com/news)\n\n---\n\n## 📦 Washington wants to export the whole American AI stack, not just the software layer\n\nAmerica's AI strategy is becoming quite readable: bundle the full stack, call it trusted, and ship it abroad before someone else does.\n\n- **The program:** On April 1, 2026, the Commerce Department opened proposals for the American AI Exports Program, inviting industry-led consortia to submit full-stack AI packages through June 30.\n- **What full-stack means here:** Commerce explicitly wants offerings that combine AI hardware, data pipelines, models, systems, financing support, and export-control engagement, all aligned with U.S. national security and foreign-policy goals.\n\n*Industrial policy has officially become a product bundle.*\n\n**Sources:** [Department of Commerce Begins Inaugural Call for Proposals for American AI Exports Program](https://www.trade.gov/press-release/department-commerce-begins-inaugural-call-proposals-american-ai-exports-program) | [Federal Register notice](https://www.trade.gov/sites/default/files/2026-04/American_AI_Exports_Call_for_Proposals_Federal_Register_Notice_%2801_Apr_2026%29.pdf)\n\n---\n\n## 🇬🇧 Britain is talking about AI sovereignty with a hardware plan and a sharper tone\n\nThe UK has moved from \"we host good labs\" to \"we need leverage in the stack before someone else decides our future for us.\"\n\n- **The message:** In a speech published April 28, 2026, UK Technology Secretary Liz Kendall argued that control over chips, compute, and AI is now fundamental to economic, energy, and defence security.\n- **The concrete step:** the government said it will develop a UK AI hardware plan to secure capability in chips and semiconductor technologies, while backing domestic AI companies and coordinating more tightly with allies.\n\n*Everyone says they do not want isolation; everyone is also quietly counting their chips.*\n\n**Sources:** [Britain must secure greater control and leverage over AI](https://www.gov.uk/government/news/britain-must-secure-greater-control-and-leverage-over-ai-to-protect-our-national-security-in-fractured-world) | [GOV.UK news](https://www.gov.uk/government/news)\n"
  }
]
